The Boolean Expression Simplifier library is an OCaml library
providing means to simplify boolean expression. The original source
code has been written at the chair of robotics and embedded systems
at Technische Universität München by Alexander Ostrovsky and is
maintained by Markus Weissmann.

The releases of the Boolean Expression Simplifier library can be
downloaded from ocamlforge. The API of the Boolean Expression
Simplifier library is also available online. The source code is
released as open source under the (new) BSD license.

Simplify your boolean expressions!
